---
/**
 * /now/ — what I'm working on right now. Updated 2026-06.
 * Following the nownownow.com convention.
 */
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const updated = '2026-06';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="now — Sam Latino"
  description="What Sam Latino is working on right now — June 2026."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-5 pt-12 pb-8 md:pt-16">
    <p class="prompt m-0 text-xs">
      <span class="prompt-user">sam@latino</span><span class="prompt-sep"
        >:</span
      ><span class="prompt-path">~</span><span class="prompt-sigil">$</span>
      <span class="text-text-muted">cat now.md</span>
    </p>

    <h1 class="mt-5 mb-0 text-2xl font-semibold md:text-3xl">now</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 mb-0 font-mono text-xs text-text-faint">
      updated {updated} &middot; <a class="no-underline hover:text-accent" href="https://nownownow.com/about">what is this?</a>
    </p>

    <hr class="my-8" />

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Building</h2>
      <p>
        Six open-source projects in various states of done. The two that are
        absorbing most of my time right now:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="/projects/longhaul/">longhaul</a> — getting the MCP server
          conformant against the 2026-07-28 release-candidate spec, which
          moved to a stateless core and a Tasks extension that changes how
          long-running operations surface to clients. The signature test
          (round-robining a task lifecycle across two independent server
          instances sharing only SQLite) is passing; polish and docs are next.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/projects/millstone/">millstone</a> — the retrieval bench harness
          is done and green; the actual corpus runs haven't executed yet. Running
          them on the local GPU server means scheduling them around other workloads
          and not fabricating numbers in the meantime. The post lands when the
          harness does.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Writing</h2>
      <p>
        Three posts are up in <a href="/writing/">writing</a>: the redcell
        security sweep, the callcheck taxonomy, and the millstone crossover
        argument. The case-study pages for each project will be updated as
        bench runs complete — the posts link to them so the gap is visible.
      </p>

      <h2>Focus</h2>
      <p>
        Agent infrastructure that runs locally. The value proposition of
        self-hosted inference gets clearer the more time you spend on the
        operational details — latency, privacy routing, cost model, the fact
        that your embedding model going stale doesn't invalidate your entire
        index. I'm working through what that means for each layer of the stack.
      </p>

      <h2>Not doing</h2>
      <p>
        Not available for contract work right now. Not on social media in any
        active way. If you want to reach me, <a href="mailto:latinosammy2@gmail.com">email</a>
        is the right channel.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
